body:
@kadaan yes, we should aim to get FindBugs running on Travis, thanks for opening: https://github.com/linkedin/gobblin/issues/770

@chavdar yes I tried to find a similar functionality in Gradle, but couldn't find much. The default config options for the findbugs plugin doesn't seem to offer anything like that: https://docs.gradle.org/current/dsl/org.gradle.api.plugins.quality.FindBugs.html

The FindBugs Gradle plugin does seem to track the info, I can't seem to determine if it exposes it or not: https://github.com/gradle/gradle/blob/master/subprojects/code-quality/src/main/groovy/org/gradle/api/plugins/quality/internal/findbugs/FindBugsResult.java (`getBugCount()`)
